    {
      "id": "aebd5c819f2334ada196e1d729bf35930ecc0ef8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2012-07-26 04:40:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nHow does this affect compatibility? I see you change the open by fid logic on the MDT, what would happen with unpatched mdt should it receive the new request like this?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "78ba95ed32722c97741c3c153e4cce026c16d839",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-07-26 06:37:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> How does this affect compatibility? I see you change the open by fid logic on the MDT, what would happen with unpatched mdt should it receive the new request like this?\n\n\nWhen new client talks with old server, the new flag of \"MDS_OPEN_BY_FID\" will not be recognized. Then the server will process the open as original logic. So no compatibility issues.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "f8589381a8fb233b0032dec7f84e59837ea0da2f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2012-07-27 05:16:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Looks good to me, approved\n\nAh, I see.\nI remember there was open by fid flag before, but I guess that was in 1.8 days.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
